### Fetch Query with Stale Time Configuration in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/reference/QueryClient.md

Demonstrates fetchQuery with a staleTime parameter to control cache validation. When staleTime is specified, the cached data is only returned if it's newer than the specified duration in milliseconds. This prevents unnecessary refetches of fresh data.

```typescript
try {
  const data = await queryClient.fetchQuery({
    queryKey,
    queryFn,
    staleTime: 10000,
  })
} catch (error) {
  console.log(error)
}
```

