### useQuery with initialData and default staleTime

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/initial-query-data.md

Shows how initialData interacts with the default staleTime configuration. With staleTime: 0 (default), the query will immediately refetch when mounted even with initialData present. This demonstrates the freshness behavior of initial data.

```typescript
// Will show initialTodos immediately, but also immediately refetch todos after mount
const result = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['todos'],
  queryFn: () => fetch('/todos'),
  initialData: initialTodos,
})
```

