### Set Initial Data with Cache Timestamp using initialDataUpdatedAt (TanStack Query)

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/initial-query-data.md

When providing `initialData` from the cache, it's recommended to also pass the source query's `dataUpdatedAt` to `initialDataUpdatedAt`. This ensures the query correctly determines its staleness, preventing artificial `staleTime` settings and ensuring proper refetching behavior based on the actual age of the initial data.

```tsx
const result = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['todos', todoId],
  queryFn: () => fetch(`/todos/${todoId}`),
  initialData: () =>
    queryClient.getQueryData(['todos'])?.find((d) => d.id === todoId),
  initialDataUpdatedAt: () =>
    queryClient.getQueryState(['todos'])?.dataUpdatedAt,
})
```

