### Prefetching Data with TanStack Query's `prefetchQuery`

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/prefetching.md

This example demonstrates how to use `queryClient.prefetchQuery` to fetch and cache data in the background. The results of this prefetch are stored in the cache like a normal query, making the data available immediately when a component later requests it.

```tsx
const prefetchTodos = async () => {
  // The results of this query will be cached like a normal query
  await queryClient.prefetchQuery({
    queryKey: ['todos'],
    queryFn: fetchTodos,
  })
}
```

