### useQuery with initialData and custom staleTime

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/initial-query-data.md

Illustrates using initialData with a custom staleTime value to control data freshness. With staleTime set to 1000ms, the data is considered fresh for that duration, preventing immediate refetching and providing better user experience.

```typescript
// Show initialTodos immediately, but won't refetch until another interaction event is encountered after 1000 ms
const result = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['todos'],
  queryFn: () => fetch('/todos'),
  initialData: initialTodos,
  staleTime: 1000,
})
