### Prefetching Infinite Queries with TanStack Query

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/prefetching.md

This snippet illustrates how to use `queryClient.prefetchInfiniteQuery` to prefetch multiple pages of an infinite query. It requires specifying `initialPageParam`, `getNextPageParam`, and the `pages` option to fetch a desired number of pages, caching them for a smoother user experience.

```tsx
const prefetchProjects = async () => {
  // The results of this query will be cached like a normal query
  await queryClient.prefetchInfiniteQuery({
    queryKey: ['projects'],
    queryFn: fetchProjects,
    initialPageParam: 0,
    getNextPageParam: (lastPage, pages) => lastPage.nextCursor,
    pages: 3 // prefetch the first 3 pages
  })
}
```

