### Manually Prime Query Cache with `setQueryData` in React Query

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/prefetching.md

This TypeScript example shows how to manually add or update data in the React Query cache using `queryClient.setQueryData`. This method is useful when you already have data available synchronously (e.g., from an initial server payload) and want to seed the cache without making an additional network request.

```tsx
queryClient.setQueryData(['todos'], todos)
```

