### Initialize TanStack Query with static initial data, staleTime, and update timestamp (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/angular/guides/initial-query-data.md

This `injectQuery` setup shows `initialTodos` instantly, using `staleTime` to control refetching behavior. Additionally, `initialDataUpdatedAt` provides a timestamp for when the initial data was last updated, allowing TanStack Query to treat it as potentially fresh for longer, even if `staleTime` is exceeded by default query behavior.

```ts
result = injectQuery(() => ({
  queryKey: ['todos'],
  queryFn: () => fetch('/todos'),
  initialData: initialTodos,
  staleTime: 60 * 1000, // 1 minute
  // This could be 10 seconds ago or 10 minutes ago
  initialDataUpdatedAt: initialTodosUpdatedTimestamp, // eg. 1608412420052
}))
```

