### Provide Initial Data from Cache with useQuery (TanStack Query)

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/initial-query-data.md

This snippet shows how to use the `initialData` option in `useQuery` to populate a new query with data retrieved from another cached query via `queryClient.getQueryData()`. This technique avoids an immediate refetch for the new query if relevant data already exists in the cache.

```tsx
const result = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['todo', todoId],
  queryFn: () => fetch('/todos'),
  initialData: () => {
    // Use a todo from the 'todos' query as the initial data for this todo query
    return queryClient.getQueryData(['todos'])?.find((d) => d.id === todoId)
  },
})
```

