### Using Single QueryClient for Prefetching

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/advanced-ssr.md

Shows an alternative approach to reuse a single QueryClient across server components for prefetching, using React's cache to scope it per request. It depends on @tanstack/react-query and React. Inputs are none required beyond the cache; outputs are the shared QueryClient instance. Limitations include unnecessary overhead from serializing the entire client each time, which may duplicate unrelated query data.

```typescript
// app/getQueryClient.tsx
import { QueryClient } from '@tanstack/react-query'
import { cache } from 'react'

// cache() is scoped per request, so we don't leak data between requests
const getQueryClient = cache(() => new QueryClient())
export default getQueryClient
```

