### Prefetch data on server in Vue component using onServerPrefetch

Source: https://github.com/tanstack/query/blob/main/docs/framework/vue/guides/ssr.md

This Vue component snippet shows how to prefetch data on the server using `onServerPrefetch` in conjunction with `useQuery` from TanStack Query. By calling `suspense` within `onServerPrefetch`, the component waits for the query to resolve on the server, ensuring data is available before the initial render. The `refetch` function allows client-side re-fetching.

```html
<!-- MyComponent.vue -->
<template>
  <div>
    <button @click="refetch">Refetch</button>
    <p>{{ data }}</p>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
  import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/vue-query'
  import { onServerPrefetch } from 'vue'

  // This will be prefetched and sent from the server
  const { refetch, data, suspense } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['todos'],
    queryFn: getTodos,
  })

  onServerPrefetch(suspense)
</script>
```
